<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB03513</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT GRANTING ADDITIONAL BENEFITS TO SOLO PARENTS AMENDING FOR THIS PURPOSE REPUBLIC ACT NO. 8972, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS THE "SOLO PARENTS WELFARE ACT OF 2000"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : HB03513
Seeks to amend the existing law to expand the coverage and benefits given to solo parents 
"WHO BEARS SOLO AND LONE PARENTING."

Provides for various discounts on: 
a) 10%, children's clothings/materials from 0 - 2 y.o.;
b) 15%, baby's milk, food and food supplements from 0 - 2 y.o.;
c) 15% medicines/medical supplements/supplies from 0 - 5 y.o.

</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ARAGONES, SOL</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-08-06</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Savellano (000 2019-08-29)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON REVISION OF LAWS ON 2019-08-13</td></tr></table>